Cell.Text: G|I've got this. Do what you need to do.
This gathering is nothing more than a boast. The Thalmor are reminding us that we're at their beck and call.
We've got troubles enough without the Thalmor and their witch-hunts.
I'd rather be back at Whiterun, but while I'm here I might as well get some real news from the other parts of Skyrim.
These Thalmor might not like to admit it, but as long as the Empire has Skyrim, the Empire has strength.
Not well at all, and I'm happy to keep it that way. | That woman and her Thalmor Justiciars have caused nothing but problems for the people of Skyrim.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyBalgruufHostTopic: How well do you know Elenwen?

Cell.Text: I am not. I have no more taste for Thalmor wine than I do for Thalmor company. | What is more, I'm away from the hold at a time when there are dragons and Stormcloaks on the loose. | There's every chance I'll return to find a pile of smoking ash where Whiterun once stood.
G|Don't presume upon our friendship. My first loyalty is to the Thalmor, as you well know.
G|Yes, that's probably for the best. I really shouldn't risk getting on Elenwen's bad side.
G|Yes, this probably isn't really the place for your little jokes.
G|Thank you. I knew you'd understand.
G|I'll try to forget you ever asked.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Hmm. Very well. I'm putting my reputation on the line for you.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyOndolomarDistractionYes: I promise. Just a joke I want to play on someone.

Cell.Text: Let's hear it.
Well... let's hear it.
My ears are always open to a friend's request.
Say on, friend. What do you need?
I'm always glad to help a friend if I can. What do you need?
Do you want to help me with something?
Oh? Something interesting, I hope?
Of course! I mean... assuming you don't want me to kill someone for you. I might have to draw the line there.
I'm listening.
What is it, my friend?

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyFriendDistractionTopic: I need your help with something.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Say no more. I was wondering what you were doing here... I'm glad to play my part.
I trust you don't presume on our friendship? I am a jarl, after all. I wouldn't want to appear foolish in front of these people.
[S] G|Nothing would please me more. I'll keep their eyes away while you do what you came here for.
Hmm. I don't want to get involved in anything beneath my dignity as jarl.
Oh... perhaps not, then. I don't think the Jarl of Solitude should be participating in a childish prank.
I don't know... I don't want to do anything that might offend Elenwen. There is a lot of money at stake, after all.
[S] G|That's it? Sure. Shouldn't be too hard. I usually end up making a fool out of myself without even trying.
[S] G|I don't even want to know, do I? But for you... all right. I'll do it.
This is very irregular. I trust that whatever you're doing doesn't compromise my position in any way?

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyFriendDistractionYes: I need you to cause a scene. Get everyone's attention for a few minutes.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Ah, I see. Very well, my friend. I'll do it.
G|Mmm, sorry. I really can't risk it. I'm sure you can find someone else with a little less dignity.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyDistractionPersuadeSiddgeir: You won't be the one to look foolish, I promise. (Persuade)

Cell.Text: [S] G|Very well. I suppose there's nothing wrong with a bit of harmless fun.
G|Sorry, but you'll have to find someone else to help you with your prank.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyDistractionPersuadeIgmund: Don't worry, I just want to play a joke on someone. (Persuade)

Cell.Text: [S] G|Oh... all right. If it's so important to you, I suppose I can help.
G|I'm sorry, but I really can't.

Node.Caption: MQ201PartyDistractionPersuadeElisif: You'd be doing me a big favor... (Persuade)

Cell.Text: [S] G|Well. Anything to relieve the boredom. As long as it doesn't get back to me.
G|I don't think so. Sorry. I would love to help you, but Elenwen can be very vindictive. I wouldn't want to get on her bad side.
